          <physDesc>
            <p>A manuscript, about 7 3/4 in. by 5 3/8, consisting of 85 leaves,
                                    of which <locus from="21" to="60">foll. 21—60</locus> are vellum, the rest paper.
                                    Most of the latter are much stained and torn, especially
                                       <locus from="1" to="13">foll. 1—13</locus>, <locus from="20">20</locus>, and
                                       <locus from="70" to="85">70—85</locus>. The quires, signed with both Greek and
                                    Syriac letters, seem to have been about 12 in number. Leaves are
                                    wanting at the beginning and end, as well as after <locus from="20">foll.
                                       20</locus>, <locus from="70">70</locus>, and <locus from="77">77</locus>. There
                                    are from 17 to 23 lines in each page.</p>
